snippet.textDisplay:
For New Fans:


BTS is a seven-member group from South Korea. They debuted (their first album was released) in 2013.

RM (Kim Namjoon) - 3:03
He is the one with a baseball cap, grey jeans, and red and black hoodie. He is the leader and a rapper in the group. He speaks fluent English and learned from watching Friends. His stage name used to be Rap Monster.

Jin (Kim Seokjin) - 0:47, 3:15
He is the one in a dark blue jacket, white shirt, and black pants, with a small mullet. He is the visual and a vocalist in the group. He has a running gag of blowing kisses to the fans and calling himself "World Wide Handsome" or WWH for short. Even though he is amazing, he sadly does not get enough screen time or singing parts. He is the oldest member.

Suga (Min Yoongi) - 1:43
He is wearing a pink sweatshirt and black jeans. He is a rapper of the group. He also produces many of BTS's songs as well as other artists'. He is known for being sleepy and a little sassy. The fans have given him the nickname "Lil Meow Meow" because of his similarity to a cat.

J-Hope (Jung Hoseok) - 1:59
He is wearing a white shirt with a blue jean jacket and matching jeans. He is a main dancer and rapper. He used to be an underground dancer before he joined BTS. He is fondly known as "Hobi" or "Our Sunshine" to the fans because of his fun and outgoing personality. He has the cutest heart-shaped smile.

Jimin (Park Jimin) - 0:23
He is wearing a blue shirt, black sweatshirt, and black sweatpants. He is a main dancer and a vocalist. He did contemporary dance before joining BTS. The fan's nickname for him is "Mochi".

V (Kim Taehyung) - 0:39
He is wearing large white pants, a big green jacket, and a beanie. He is a main dancer and a vocalist. Even though his stage name is "V", he is mostly called Tae. He has a very deep voice. When he was younger he played the saxophone, but he stopped because it made his mouth hurt.

Jungkook (Jeon Junkook) - 0:55
He is wearing all black, with a big jacket, and his hair is black with blue tips. He is the main vocalist, main dancer, and maknae (youngest). Jungkook joined BTS when he was still in high school, and all of the other members attended his graduation. He is known as the golden maknae because he is literally good at everything.

snippet.textDisplay: Thank you Mr. Corden for orchestrating Homefest.  Your intention to gather different artist and show them at their home in hopes of raising donations for two necessary causes and give people some distraction from the situation we are all in is very heartfelt.  I wish all viewers got the true core of your message - let this pandemic bring out the best of people, unity, by supporting one another...BTS members, at a young age when you debuted, you have faced adversity every step of the way  - including negative, hurtful comments...but you still managed to pull through, together.  The positive messages you send through your music, speeches, connect BTS, etc. are extraordinary.  Really extraordinary.  Like the lyrics in your song...when people forget to be respectful and just plain mean...remember...you are not only seven anymore!  BTS Thank you!  Mr. Corden and all the artist and staff that participated in Homefest - Thank you very much!
